headline: 3 Reasons NTAP is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, NetApp’s stock price fell to $102.35. Shareholders have lost 17.1% of their capital, disappointing when considering the S&P 500 was flat. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.

headline: Q1 Earnings Highs And Lows: HP (NYSE:HPQ) Vs The Rest Of The Hardware & Infrastructure Stocks
summary: The end of the earnings season is always a good time to take a step back and see who shined (and who not so much). Let’s take a look at how hardware & infrastructure stocks fared in Q1, starting with HP (NYSE:HPQ).
